    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Cython optimize `len()` based on container passed as argument. It currently does not work for subscripted types (`list[...], ...`). See comments below\r\n\r\n> There is one additional issue. This PR compiles `Code.py` with following line:\r\n> \r\n> ```c\r\n> __pyx_t_3 = PyObject_Length(__pyx_v_int_constants_by_bytesize);\r\n> ```\r\n> \r\n> instead of what we have in master:\r\n> \r\n> ```c\r\n> __pyx_t_3 = __Pyx_PyList_GET_SIZE(__pyx_v_int_constants_by_bytesize);\r\n> ```\r\n> \r\n> The affected line is following:\r\n> \r\n> https://github.com/cython/cython/blob/7dda0262a7954a076129d2b4f105696e75eb3bce/Cython/Compiler/Code.py#L2391\r\n\r\nOK culprit is not related to this PR but here: https://github.com/cython/cython/blob/7dda0262a7954a076129d2b4f105696e75eb3bce/Cython/Compiler/Optimize.py#L2885-L2895\r\n\r\n_Originally posted by @matusvalo in https://github.com/cython/cython/issues/7686#issuecomment-4435345854_\r\n            ",
